  description="Wine and oenology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHIANTI (12pts), SYRAH (11pts), MERLOT (8pts). Wine vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble wine words, wine scrabble terms, merlot scrabble points, syrah scrabble, chianti scrabble word, oenology vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Wine — Oenology Terms That Score Big","description":"Wine and oenology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHIANTI (12pts), SYRAH (11pts), MERLOT (8pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-wine"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MERLOT a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MERLOT scores 8 points (M=3, E=1, R=1, L=1, O=1, T=1). It's a red wine grape variety originally from Bordeaux. Valid in SOWPODS, MERLOT uses common tiles making it easy to play on most boards."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is SYRAH worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SYRAH scores 11 points (S=1, Y=4, R=1, A=1, H=4). It's a dark-skinned grape variety used in red wines. The Y (4pts) and H (4pts) tiles together contribute 8 of the 11 total points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CHIANTI valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. CHIANTI scores 12 points (C=3, H=4, I=1, A=1, N=1, T=1, I=1). It's a red wine from Tuscany, Italy. The C (3pts) and H (4pts) make the opening combination worth 7 points alone."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Wine — Oenology Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Wine culture contributes surprisingly strong Scrabble words. Grape varieties and winemaking terms carry premium letters — H in SYRAH, C+H in CHIANTI, and plenty of uncommon letter combinations. Whether you're a sommelier or just enjoy a glass, these words belong in your Scrabble vocabulary.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHIANTI (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SYRAH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MERLOT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PINOT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Wine Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CHIANTI — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, H=4, I=1, A=1, N=1, T=1, I=1 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A dry red wine from Italy's Tuscany region. At 7 letters, CHIANTI qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus if you use all your tiles — turning 12 base points into 62. The CH opening is powerful on a DLS.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍷 SYRAH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · S=1, Y=4, R=1, A=1, H=4 · Red grape variety</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍇 MERLOT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · M=3, E=1, R=1, L=1, O=1, T=1 · Bordeaux grape</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥂 BRUT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 pts · B=3, R=1, U=1, T=1 · Very dry champagne</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫙 VINTAGE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · V=4, I=1, N=1, T=1, A=1, G=2, E=1 · Year's harvest</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Wine Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TANNIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DECANT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VARIETAL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CORKED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOUQUET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOMMELIER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Wine Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHIANTI is a bingo word:</span> At exactly 7 letters, playing CHIANTI using all your tiles earns the 50-point bonus. Hold C, H, I, A, N, T, I and you have a guaranteed bingo worth 62 points total.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SYRAH pairs Y with H:</span> Both Y (4pts) and H (4pts) are mid-value tiles that often sit unused. SYRAH burns both in one 5-letter word, clearing your rack while scoring 11 points minimum.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BOUQUET is the hidden gem:</span> At 18 points (B=3, O=1, U=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1, T=1), BOUQUET is a Q-with-U word that many players overlook. It's the highest-scoring wine term available.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Wine vocabulary is rich in <span class="text-white font-medium">H and Y tiles</span> — the 4-point letters that often get stuck on racks. SYRAH, CHIANTI, and others burn these tiles efficiently. BOUQUET (18pts) is also a top-tier Q dump hiding in plain sight.</p>
      </div>
